args:
Peng Lai, too, is concerned about the problem at
the dragon-vein spring. In order to ascertain the
whereabouts of the one responsible, he pours
his own mana into the earth, which the party
then follows to the culprit.
Is this really the dragon-vein spring?\nIt sure doesn't look like much.
There is supposed to be a beautiful\nspring here. I am certain of it!
I suppose if it has dried up completely,\nthis is what we would see.
The atmosphere here is really tense—\nmy goose bumps are getting goose bumps!
And yet, there's this super calm flow\nof chi running under the surface...
That chi is Peng Lai's.\nHe should be nearby.
Everyone, look over there!\nIs THAT the dragon?!
Ooo hoo! That's some fine work, Ku Hai!\nLooks like you sussed out all them\nfighters I was after!
I reckon you'll be wantin' a treat for all\nthat hard work. Now where'd I go and\nput that there lollipop...?
Mock me not! I am no child.
Ooh hoo hoo! Everyone from Peng Lai is\nmy child, no matter how old they get.
I was curious what sort of majestic\npresence awaited when I heard we were\ndealing with a dragon of legend, but...
He's like some jovial old man!
Right then! Guess I should go get the\ngood crockery for m'honored guests.\nLemme just... Muh?!
You there! With the fancy hair!\nYou bear the blood of dragons, so you do!
Ooh hoo hoo! When you're old like me,\nyou'll find your head filled with all kinds\nof facts—most of 'em useless as mud.
It's a lucky thing to see a whippersnapper\nlike you come strollin' through m'door.
Lucky? Wait, so does that mean you\nDIDN'T summon me here in a dream?
Hmm? I'm afraid I don't know anything\nabout a dream.
It has been a long time, Peng Lai.
Well, if it ain't Su Fang! I sure am lookin'\nforward to your pyroblossoms this year.
I am...honored. However, with the\ndragon-vein spring in its current state...
Yeah, she's a real mess. Still, it ain't\nthe first time she's looked like this.
A hundred years ago, before the town\nof Peng Lai was founded, this place\nlooked just like this.
Turned out it was 'cause of some fiend\nwhat was drinkin' up all the mana.

Me and Xu Fu went and sealed the fiend
away and restored the spring, which
allowed us to create the town all you
folks enjoy so much now.
You sealed it, but didn't defeat it?
Yeah, he was a tough ol' nut to crack!\nWe ended up havin' to just seal him away\nwhen we couldn't defeat him for good.
Could our current disaster also be\nlinked to this fiend's influence?

I do wonder about his state, but if
he were really back, we'd be seein'
a heap'a trouble bigger than just
one dried-out old spring.
Easy there! Let an old dragon think a spell!\nNow, by my reckonin', there's some foul\ncritter what's disturbin' the flow of mana.
So if we follow the flow from this place,\nwe oughta be able to track down whatever\nthe problem is.
I'm not certain the current amount of mana\nis sufficient for us to be ABLE to follow it.
Then we just gotta give 'er a boost!
There's mana flowing from his body!

Pretty slick trick, eh? Now if y'all just
go ahead and follow that there mana,
it'll lead right to the source of all this
durn mischief.
Peng Lai's mana is flowing that way!
Go on now, young'uns! Get this thing done!
